## Overview

This branch contains an independent evaluation of the **SKAB (Skoltech Anomaly Benchmark)** dataset to determine its suitability for supervised binary fault classification in a predictive maintenance context.

The evaluation was conducted to compare SKAB against the Kaggle Pump Sensor dataset and provide evidence-based reasoning for the team's final dataset decision. The work covers the full pipeline — from raw data loading through to model training, evaluation, and a written verdict.

---

## Dataset

**SKAB v0.9** is a publicly available benchmark dataset collected from a real industrial pump testbed at Skoltech, Russia. It contains multivariate time-series sensor recordings sampled at 1 Hz (one reading per second).

### Files Used

| Source | Files | Total Rows | Fault Rows | Fault % |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| anomaly-free | 1 file | 9,401 | 0 | 0.0% |
| valve1 | 16 files (0.csv – 15.csv) | 18,162 | 6,309 | 34.7% |
| valve2 | 4 files (0.csv – 3.csv) | 4,312 | 1,517 | 35.2% |
| **Total** | **21 files** | **31,875** | **7,826** | **24.6%** |

- **anomaly-free** contains normal pump operation with no faults — used as the normal class baseline
- **valve1** captures fault scenarios caused by closing the valve at the pump inlet
- **valve2** captures fault scenarios caused by closing the valve at the pump outlet

### Sensor Features (8 columns)

| Sensor | Description |
|---|---|
| Accelerometer1RMS | Vibration acceleration — sensor 1 (g) |
| Accelerometer2RMS | Vibration acceleration — sensor 2 (g) |
| Current | Amperage on the electric motor (A) |
| Pressure | Pressure in the loop after the pump (Bar) |
| Temperature | Engine body temperature (°C) |
| Thermocouple | Fluid temperature in the circulation loop (°C) |
| Voltage | Voltage on the electric motor (V) |
| Volume Flow RateRMS | Flow rate root mean square (L/min) |

