## Dataset Fitness Verdict

| Criterion | Result |
|---|---|
| F1 >= 80% target |  MET — Random Forest at 89.55% |
| No missing values |  Clean data |
| Meaningful fault labels | Present in valve1 and valve2 |
| Class imbalance manageable | 3:1 ratio handled well with SMOTE |
| Data volume |  31,875 rows — smaller than ideal |
| Fault variety |  Only valve closure faults |
| Experiment continuity |  Short individual experiments (~20 min each) |

**Conclusion:** The SKAB dataset is capable of supporting supervised fault classification and meets the F1 target. However, its limited size and fault variety make the **Kaggle Pump Sensor dataset** (220,000 rows, continuous recording, richer fault types) a stronger primary choice for the project's final model.

